  <!-- ═══ WHAT THE MODEL DOESN'T CAPTURE ═══ -->
  <h2>Risks & What the Model Misses</h2>

  <h3>Upside risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Uninterrupted M&A success:</strong> Amphenol's growth has historically been fueled by hyper-effective, decentralized acquisitions. A massive string of further successful consolidations could blast past our 10% growth rate.</li>
    <li><strong>AI infrastructure boom:</strong> High-speed optical and copper interconnects are vital for AI server racks. Surging data center buildouts could cause persistent revenue beats.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Downside risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Debt load:</strong> Total debt surged to $15.5B in 2025 following acquisitions. While covered by strong cash flows, an unexpected sustained spike in refinancing rates could pressure equity value.</li>
    <li><strong>Cyclical downturn:</strong> Industrial and broadband markets are cyclical. A global manufacturing recession would constrain short-term cash flows aggressively.</li>
    <li><strong>M&A indigestion:</strong> Buying massive entities like the mobile networks business of CommScope brings integration risks. A failure to realize synergies would compress margins.</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
